{{Hinduism by country}}

{{Disputed|date=June 2015}}'''Hinduism in Egypt''' is a [[minority religion]] practiced mainly by the [[India]]n [[expatriate]]s and workers in the nation. According to the [[2012 Constitution of Egypt|constitution of Egypt]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Egyptian voters back new constitution in referendum|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-20842487|work=BBC News|publisher=British Broadcast Corporation|accessdate=25 December 2012}}</ref> there are approximately 57%{{Citation needed|date=March 2015}} [[Hindu]]s of Indian origin in [[Egypt]], and they are 90% of the Indian population in the country.<ref>[http://www.egypttoday.com/article.aspx?ArticleID=8517 Color Me Indian] Egypt Today - June 2009</ref>

After the [[2011 Egyptian revolution|Egyptian unrest]], starting from 2011, many Hindus went back to India.{{cn|date=September 2017}}

